00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:53,000
 That would have been a more modern translation of what's happening here.

313
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:57,000
 And yet what he is saying is not out of touch, but very in touch with the people he's speaking to.

314
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:00,000
 Because the nation of Israel, they were an agrarian society.

315
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:07,000
 They were great at working the land and harvesting a crop and taking up its yield.

316
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:14,000
 They were familiar with all of the work it took to actually bear fruit from the earth.

317
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:16,000
 As any good farmer knows, and these people would have known as well,

318
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:20,000
 it does you no good to plant seed unless you have first plowed soil.

319
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:24,000
 That's what Hosea means when he says, "Break up your fallow ground."

320
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:28,000
 What's fallow ground? Fallow ground is dormant ground.

321
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,000
 It's ground that has gone undisturbed.

322
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:34,000
 It's filled with weeds and thistles and rocks and debris.

323
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,000
 It's been untouched.

324
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,000
 And there's a good reason for it.

325
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:41,000
 The nation of Israel would do this because they would want their soil

326
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:46,000
 to replenish in terms of its nutrients, to prevent disease.

327
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:49,000
 And you've learned this in grade school science or social studies.

328
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,000
 It's called crop rotation, people.

329
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,000
 What do you do with fallow ground?

330
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:57,000
 You've got to break it up because though it is nutrient rich,

331
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:00,000
 it is hard as a rock.

332
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,000
 It has to be loosened.

333
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:05,000
 It's not accommodating for planting.

334
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:09,000
 It will not give you any growth because it is already overgrown.

335
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:11,000
 When my wife and I lived in Houston,

336
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:15,000
 we had an amazing front yard in our very first home.

