00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:08,000
 but to actually impact it for a difference

535
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:11,000
 and begin to till up the soil of your soul

536
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:14,000
 because until you do, you will not be able to sow into your satisfaction,

537
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:16,000
 which is where Hosea goes next.

538
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:20,000
 He says, "Sow righteousness. Reap steadfast love."

539
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:23,000
 Something I think we could all agree that we want in life is to be approved of.

540
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:25,000
 We want to be accepted by others.

541
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:27,000
 We want to be loved in this world.

542
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:29,000
 Listen, we're not wrong for wanting that.

543
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:31,000
 That's not a bad desire.

544
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:33,000
 You're not wrong for wanting for it.

545
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:37,000
 You're wrong in light of where you might be searching for it,

546
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:40,000
 which was the case for the nation of Israel in this moment.

547
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:42,000
 At the time that Hosea is prophesying here,

548
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:45,000
 the nation of Israel was being led by King Jeroboam II.

549
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:48,000
 On the surface, Jeroboam's reign was marked by

550
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:50,000
 prosperity and national security.

551
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:55,000
 He expanded the borders of Israel to a place that had not reached the same extent

552
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:58,000
 until the time of Solomon himself.

553
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:00,000
 He had great political prowess.

554
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,000
 He had successful military campaigns.

555
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:07,000
 But underneath it all, Jeroboam II did what was evil on the side of the Lord.

556
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:12,000
 He led the nation into idolatry for 40-plus years.

557
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:14,000
 What was the result of that?

558
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:17,000
 The people of Israel, they were searching for satisfaction in all the wrong places.

559
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:21,000
 They were looking for love and acceptance and approval in all the wrong places.

560
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:24,000
 They were worshipping at the feet of false gods instead of the one true God.

561
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:29,000
 They were gratifying their sinful desire as opposed to the desire of the Spirit.

562
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:34,000
 And what they found is they were, instead of investing in the renewal of their spirit,

563
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:38,000
 they were investing in the rejection of God's spirit.

564
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:40,000
 What's the point that Hosea is making?

565
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:42,000
 It's our second point.

566
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:46,000
 You reap in life what you sow in the soul.

567
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:51,000
 You reap in life what you sow in the soul.

568
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:53,000
 Let me explain what I mean.

