 Haven't we settled for less long enough?

737
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:28,000
 Like there's more on the table. Don't you want that?

738
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:31,000
 Don't you want a relationship with God that's more?

739
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:35,000
 That's more than just a faith of fact.

740
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:38,000
 But it's actually a faith of feeling.

741
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:42,000
 Like don't you want a relationship with God

742
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:46,000
 that's not just intellectually impressive or emotionally charged?

743
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:49,000
 It's experientially powerful.

744
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:51,000
 Don't you want that? I want that.

745
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:54,000
 That's why I'm doing this. We're preaching this.

746
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:58,000
 I remember when we, Brooke and I, made our way to Dallas, Texas to consider God.

747
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:00,000
 Would you even bring us here?

748
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:02,000
 Is this where you want us to go?

749
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:04,000
 You're doing a good thing where we are, God.

750
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:06,000
 I'm not just like ready to up and leave.

751
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:09,000
 Like I love where we're at. You're doing a good work.

752
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:12,000
 You're already moving there, God. Why would you bring us here instead?

753
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:16,000
 You must prove to me that it's here you're moving as well.

754
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:18,000
 And as I preached on the stage for the very first time,

755
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:21,000
 and I came back and I preached on the stage for the very second time,

756
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:23,000
 I found that God was moving here.

757
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:28,000
 And as I was processing that reality, God, you're moving.

758
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:33,000
 In that soft, still voice that the Spirit only speaks,

759
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:38,000
 I sensed Him say, "Kylin, you haven't begun to see me move.

760
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:42,000
 You have not begun to see me move.

761
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:47,000
 There's more in this room than you realize.

762
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:50,000
 But only I can unlock it.

763
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:53,000
 Call these people to me.

764
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:59,000
 Tell them that it's time to seek after me.

765
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:04,000
 And remind them I have already sought after them first."

766
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:11,000
 You see, we're convinced that we seek a God who has sought after us,

767
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:14,000
 for He sent Jesus Christ Himself.

768
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:17,000
 We break up our hard-heartedness,

769
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:21,000
 for Christ has come to give you a new heart,

770
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:27,000
 one that is worthy of protecting.

771
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:30,000
 We reap in life what we sow in the soul,

772
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:35,000
 for Jesus has reaped in death to save your soul.

773
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:39,000
 And we seek the Lord, not settling for less,

774
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:42,000
 for Christ sought you,

775
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:45,000
 because He wouldn't settle for anything less Himself.

776
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:48,000
 He wanted you.

777
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:50,000
 But I'm not worthy, Kylin.

778
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:52,000
 You are correct.

779
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:53,000
 You are not worthy.

780
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:55,000
 But He is.

781
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:59,000
 And by saving people who face the very worst of odds,

782
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:02,000
 He gets greater glory.

783
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:05,000
 He moves towards the people that do not deserve Him to move towards them,

784
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:08,000
 that we might be affirmed, "Yes, God, we need You.

785
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:10,000
 We cannot save ourselves.

786
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:12,000
 And, God, we want You.

787
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:16,000
 We want You because You would come for us."

788
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:20,000
 Let us be a people here at the porch that call out our need

789
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:25,000
 and call out our desire that You, God, and You, God alone,

790
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:32,000
 are worthy of seeking and we're willing to seek right now.

791
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:36,000
 It's time, porch, to take these things as serious as they are.

792
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:39,000
 It's time to believe beyond where we've been.

793
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:41,000
 It's time to make a change in our own lives.

794
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:45,000
 I will boldly ask you, if you will not make a change in your own life,

795
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:47,000
 then make some space instead,

796
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:50,000
 because I want this to be a room filled with people

797
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:52,000
 that are desiring after God,

798
00:43:52,000 --> 00:43:54,000
 taking Christ's claims seriously,

799
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:57,000
 and walking in hot pursuit after Him,

800
00:43:57,000 --> 00:44:00,000
 believing that, yes, life everlasting will be amazing,

801
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:03,000
 but life everlasting has come crashing into our present moment,

802
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:05,000
 and we can be a part of it.

803
00:44:05,000 --> 00:44:08,000
 I don't want to simply look back and realize,

804
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:10,000
 "Man, the window was open."

805
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:13,000
 I want to realize that window was one I lived within.

806
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:16,000
 I don't want to look back with hindsight and say,

807
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:17,000
 "Man, God really moved there."

808
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:20,000
 I want to live into this moment and believe that,

809
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:23,000
 "Man, God and I were both there together.

810
00:44:23,000 --> 00:44:25,000
 This is what's on the table."

811
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:30,000
 God, please, would You work in these people

812
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:35,000
 and bring them to a place where they take God, You, seriously.

813
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:37,000
 This message is imperfect.

814
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:40,000
 We, God, on this stage are imperfect,

815
00:44:40,000 --> 00:44:44,000
 but God, You are so perfect.

816
00:44:44,000 --> 00:44:47,000
 They do not need us. They need You.

817
00:44:47,000 --> 00:44:49,000
 We, God, are not worthy of wanting,

818
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:52,000
 but You, God, are worthy of wanting.

819
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:55,000
 And God, I pray You would know here in this place,

820
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:58,000
 we hunger for You.

821
00:44:58,000 --> 00:45:00,000
 We want for You, God.

822
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:04,000
 We see what You're doing across the globe,

823
00:45:04,000 --> 00:45:07,000
 and we want it right here.

824
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:11,000
 We don't want to just look back, God, and see what You did.

825
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:18,000
 We want to live now, God, and experience it ourselves.

826
00:45:18,000 --> 00:45:22,000
 At the right time, Christ, You died for the ungodly.

827
00:45:22,000 --> 00:45:30,000
 It is our time to live for the only God worthy.

828
00:45:30,000 --> 00:45:35,000
 It's to Your glory we pray, in Jesus' name, amen.

829
00:45:35,000 --> 00:45:45,000
 Hey, porch, you can stand to your feet.

830
00:45:45,000 --> 00:45:48,000
 We're going to go back into a little bit of worship,

831
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:50,000
 but some of you, you really need to work through

832
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:53,000
 and process whatever it is God is stirring up in you.

833
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:55,000
 Now is the right time to do it.

834
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:58,000
 Now is the time to break up the hard soil.

835
00:45:58,000 --> 00:46:00,000
 We're here to help you do the work.

836
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:02,000
 We would love to pray with you if we can,

837
00:46:02,000 --> 00:46:08,000
 but let this not be a moment where we feel awkward about making a move.

838
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:10,000
 He is on the move.

839
00:46:10,000 --> 00:46:13,000
 Let us respond in kind.

